REACTION   ((1-H-1(33-AS-73,G)34-SE-74,,SIG)=
           (33-AS-73(P,G)34-SE-74,,SIG))
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Experimental uncertainty, it was assumed
           to be Gaussian. The uncertainty associated with the
           ratio Y/e (Yield/efficiency=Total number of
           reactions) was largely dominated by the statistical
           uncertainty of the background subtraction. The
           overall uncertainties for Y/e were ~24% and ~74% for
           the 3.7 and 3.1 MeV/nucleon laboratory system beam
           energies, respectively.
           (ERR-S) For the measurement with beam energy of 3.7
           MeV/nucleon->2.95 c.m., the statistical uncertainty
           was ~18%. Unfortunately, the second measurement, with
           beam energy of 3.1 MeV/nucleon-> 2.35 c.m., suffered
           from very low statistics, and the associated
           uncertainty was ~72%.
           (ERR-1) ~6% uncertainty introduced from the
           normalization method of the empty cell data.
           (ERR-2) ~13% uncertainty from the different
           statistical model inputs used in RAINIER code.
           (ERR-3) The target areal density uncertainty of ~5%.
           (ERR-4) The number of projectiles introduced an ~8%
           uncertainty to the total incident particles.
